entries.femaleVariant: <kiroshi l="mex" o="¡Pinches hijos de la chingada madre!" t="Motherfucking cocksuckers!" b="" a=""/>
You think this is my fault?
Calm down. Things like this happen.
Calm down. Sometimes these things happen.
[Poke iguana] We should sell it.
You know your iguanas?
<mothertongue l="mex" m="¡No mames!" b="" a=" A real iguana! A, uh, Lesser Antillean, I think."/>
Think you can make some money on it?
entries.maleVariant: You think you can make some money on it?

entries.femaleVariant: Yeah, partner. We'll go halfsies.
Lesser Antil-what?
Yeah! Watched a thing on TV about 'em. Went extinct like thirty years ago. They're from the Lesser Antilles.
It's kind of a shame, though... I always wanted a pet.
Got the name Manny all thought out.
Hey, by the way... you, uh, got any plans for what you'll be doin' in Night City?
I have no plans at the moment.
Why do you ask?
Why do you ask?
If you think this is my fault, at least have the balls to say so.
This?! What kinda shit happens?!
I don't know yet. Is it?!
Sure. Think it'll make us happy.
"Us"?
I don't have any plans. I've spent the last years traveling between states with my nomad family.
entries.maleVariant: I don't have any plans. I've spent the last years travelin' between states with my nomad family.

entries.femaleVariant: You come a long way, my scaly friend.
Ah, prolly be waitin' for you somewhere, eh?
No. We decided to go our separate ways.
That must be tough, huh? Havin' no one to go back to?
Cause I got this feelin' you got a lotta time... an' nothin' to spend it on.
And NC ain't a city that lets you get by without buddies.
Hey, c'mon. 'S nothin'. We got chemistry, you an' me. Be a cryin' shame to waste it... partner.
I never said I needed help.
Thanks.
I don't need help.
Hey, c'mon. It's nothin'. We got chemistry, you an' me. Be a cryin' shame to waste it... partner.
Thanks, much appreciated.
But don't you worry. Lemme help you find digs. You gotta live somewhere.
Border security tipped off the corporation that we have their cargo.
What's the deal with these borderlies flippin' us the finger as they fuckin' please?! With no consequences!
He took a risk. He assumed we didn't have a clan backing us, and he was right.
Oh shit.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Pendejamente ridículo..." b="Pff... " a=" So what now?"/>
I don't know if your client's gonna be happy gettin' an open package. Usually means trouble.
entries.maleVariant: I dunno if your client's gonna be happy gettin' an open package. It usually means trouble.

entries.femaleVariant: [Open] Let's peek away.
Fuck the client. You gotta start workin' for yourself sometime. No commission, no middlemen.
Says Arasaka on the crate... We are robbin' some heavy hitters.
entries.maleVariant: It says Arasaka on the crate... We are robbing some heavy hitters.

entries.femaleVariant: Then maybe we'll make some heavy money.
And I need to know what I'm sellin' if I'm gonna try to find a new buyer.
Any decent fixer'll find a loaded gonk interested in a rare gem like this.
They almost tagged our asses! That what you call smugglin'?!
<kiroshi l="mex" o="¡Chingado!" t="Fuck!" b="" a=""/>
It was supposed to go smooth. No problems!
You pay my transport fee.
We've crossed the border. Now you pay me, and we go our separate ways.
I could ask you the same question – will you keep whining, or will we put a bow on this thing?
entries.maleVariant: I could ask the same question – will you keep whinin', or will we put a bow on this thing?

entries.femaleVariant: I could ask the same question.
Uh, I ain't gonna lie... I'm a bit light. I can't pay you now.
Ah, and you just figured I would sit by patiently?
entries.maleVariant: Huh. And you just figured I would sit by patiently.

entries.femaleVariant: Have somethin' for you once I collect my scrap for this corpo crap we're carryin'.
Actually, I wasn't gonna pay you at all. Was just gonna bust ass and disappear soon as we crossed over. But…
You tricked me.
You tricked me.
I appreciate the honesty.
I appreciate the honesty.
Oh, well, apologies for offending the spotless moral code of a smuggler.
Ah, thanks.
So, what's next?
Now we take a peek inside.
You're all right.
Open it.
You're all right, too.
OK, partner. Time to grab the lizard and scurry outta here.
You know what, Jackie? You're not all bad yourself.
<mothertongue l="mex" m="chica" b="Ha-aw, you don't mean that, " a="."/>
entries.maleVariant: <mothertongue l="mex" m="mano" b="Ha-haw, you don't mean that, " a="."/>

entries.femaleVariant: [Shake Jackie's hand] Let's move, partner.
What now?
<mothertongue l="mex" m="Vamos" b="" a=", let's have a look inside this box."/>
Shouldn't touch the merchandise.
Aww, cuddly little fucker.
Hey!
[Get out]
S'important to have people you can turn to. Y'know, like, uh, family. Maybe you'll find your own down in Night City.
